### Project layout

This is a Go package (library) project.

- Exported package code lives at the project root.
- Tests are colocated alongside the source files they test.
- Keep exported identifiers minimal.
- Write doc comments for exported types/functions where the intent is not obvious.
- Prefer smaller packages with clear responsibilities; avoid cyclic dependencies.
- Keep packages small and focused; split into subpackages when responsibilities diverge.

